<TEXT>
more than 5000 doctors at staterun 
hospitals ended a 47dayold strike sunday that had paralyzed 
medical care to the citys poor 
the doctors are to return to work monday according to 
negotiators for the government and the junior doctors federation 
the agreement ending the strike was signed following negotiations 
that stretched through the night the doctors had demanded pay 
raises higher allowances for not being allowed to maintain private 
practices and schedules for promotion 
